This code is outdated and should NOT be used. See US_EPA_krige_AQS repository for the most up-to-date version. 
- Kate O'Dell, 08.06.2021

ColoradoPM-Krige
	Github repository for scripts used to krige daily PM2.5 concentrations from EPA AQS monitors in the Colorado Front Range. 

This folder contains the following python scripts:

eval_kriging.py - makes figures to evaluate kriging output

find_VGPparams_DEN.py - used to find the kriging variogram parameters

krige_aqs_DEN_mtncutoff.py - script where data is kriged

npz2netCDF.py - takes npz files output by kriging code and writes a netCDF file

sample_grid.py - plot the kriging grid
